</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF856A3AF81A900416CDBC59" pageId="126" pageNumber="885" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF856A3AF81A900416CDBC59" blockId="126.[2019,2616,1511,1939]" pageId="126" pageNumber="885">
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF856A3AF81A900416DCBD4C" authorityName="Sody" authorityYear="1936" box="[2022,2268,1629,1662]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="126" pageNumber="885" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="collinus">Scotophilus collinus</taxonomicName>
has often been included under S. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF856A3AF78C90DC16B6BD94" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1821" box="[2160,2230,1669,1702]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="126" pageNumber="885" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kuhlii">kuhlii</taxonomicName>
, but it is generally recognized as a distinct species based on morphology. There might be two subspecies of S. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF856A3AF7F790A2166CBC2E" authorityName="Sody" authorityYear="1936" box="[2059,2156,1787,1820]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="126" pageNumber="885" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="collinus">collinus</taxonomicName>
based on morphometric analyses: one In the east and the other in the west. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
